data.title: U.S. Army Southern European Task Force, Africa holds patching ceremony during quarterly All-Hands brief [Image 7 of 13]
data.meta_description: U.S. Army Southern European Task Force, Africa (SETAF-AF) senior leaders pose for a group photo showing off the new SETAF-AF patch during the quarterly SETAF-AF All-Hands brief at Casema Ederle, Vicenza, Italy, June 21, 2024. The new SETAF-AF shoulder sleeve insignia was authorized on Apr. 1, 2024 by the U.S. Army. SETAF-AF provides U.S. Africa Command and U.S. Army Europe & Africa a dedicated headquarters to synchronize Army activities in Africa and scalable crisis response options in Africa and Europe. (U.S. Army photo by Spc. Cade Castillo)
